  "text": "Indeed, the most established management paradigm for the treatment of alopecia in the male is finasteride [CITATION_1] . First approved in 1992 in the treatment of benign prostatic hypertrophy, finasteride was approved for the treatment of alopecia in 1997 at a dose of 1 mg daily (propecia ® ) [CITATION_2] .",
